abstract: New rules will allow American companies to open locations and hire workers in Cuba and facilitate financial transactions between the nations.
snippet: New rules will allow American companies to open locations and hire workers in Cuba and facilitate financial transactions between the nations.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The White House on Friday announced wide-ranging changes to loosen travel, commerce and investment restrictions on Cuba, moving to fulfill President Obama’s goal of breaking down barriers between Washington and Havana even as the American embargo remains in place.

abstract: The Justice Department will not block Expedia’s $1.3 billion purchase of Orbitz, another travel-booking site.
snippet: The Justice Department will not block Expedia’s $1.3 billion purchase of Orbitz, another travel-booking site.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Justice Department will not try to block the acquisition of the travel booking site Orbitz by its larger rival Expedia, clearing the way for the companies to complete the $1.3 billion merger announced earlier this year.

abstract: Mike Lee, the junior senator from Utah who helped lead the government shutdown effort, has a reputation of defying party leaders as well as cooperating with Democrats on libertarian-leaning policy.
snippet: Mike Lee, the junior senator from Utah who helped lead the government shutdown effort, has a reputation of defying party leaders as well as cooperating with Democrats on libertarian-leaning policy.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — As meetings among congressional colleagues go, the one last month in which Republican senators confronted Mike Lee, a freshman from Utah, was among the most contentious in years.

abstract: The public supports ending the embargo and some in Congress are taking steps to make that happen.
snippet: The public supports ending the embargo and some in Congress are taking steps to make that happen.
lead_paragraph: In 1962, the year Bob Dylan released his first album, Marilyn Monroe died of an overdose and Nelson Mandela was imprisoned, the American government began imposing an economic embargo on Cuba in an effort to subvert Fidel Castro.

abstract: A long-delayed vote for a new attorney general has been scheduled for Thursday, after senators announced a compromise on legislation that had entangled Ms. Lynch’s nomination.
snippet: A long-delayed vote for a new attorney general has been scheduled for Thursday, after senators announced a compromise on legislation that had entangled Ms. Lynch’s nomination.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — After weeks of difficult negotiations, the Senate on Tuesday reached an agreement to clear the way for the long-delayed confirmation of Loretta E. Lynch to replace Eric H. Holder Jr. as the attorney general.

abstract: Without her, the Democratic race would be chaotic, which helps explain why she enjoys such support within the party.
snippet: Without her, the Democratic race would be chaotic, which helps explain why she enjoys such support within the party.
lead_paragraph: We’re on record here at The Upshot as believing that Hillary Clinton is in an extremely strong position to win the Democratic nomination. And as Brendan Nyhan has explained, the furor over her private email account is likely to affect far fewer voters than may now appear to be the case.
